definitions.definition: To make or cut a channel or groove in.
To direct or guide along a desired course.
examples: We will channel the traffic to the left with these cones.

definitions.definition: To serve as a medium for.
examples: She was channeling the spirit of her late husband, Seth.
definitions.label_groups: transitive , of a spirit, as of a dead person

definitions.definition: To follow as a model, especially in a performance.
examples: He was trying to channel President Reagan, but the audience wasn't buying it.
When it is my turn to sing karaoke, I am going to channel Ray Charles.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To make or cut a channel or groove in.
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To direct or guide along a desired course.
( transitive , of a spirit, as of a dead person ) To serve as a medium for.
( transitive ) To follow as a model, especially in a performance.
